SIMPLE: clandestine
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Clandestine
<hw>Clan*des"tine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>clandestinus</ets>, fr. <ets>clam</ets> secretly; akin to
<ets>celare</ets>, E. <ets>conceal</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>clandestin</ets>.]</ety> <def>Conducted with secrecy; withdrawn
from public notice, usually for an evil purpose; kept secret; hidden;
private; underhand; <as>as, a <ex>clandestine</ex> marriage</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Locke.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Hidden; secret; private; concealed; underhand;
sly; stealthy; surreptitious; furtive; fraudulent.</syn></p>

<p> -- <wordforms><wf>Clan*des"tine*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Clan*des"tine*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clandestinity</ent>⟦br⟧
